---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const tool1 = "Mailchimp";
const tool2 = "Klaviyo";
const category = "Email Marketing";
const verdict = "Mailchimp";
const verdictReason = "for most bootstrapped founders getting started";
---
<Base 
  title={`${tool1} vs ${tool2}`}
  description={`${tool1} vs ${tool2}: an honest, no-BS comparison for bootstrapped founders. Which one is actually worth it?`}
>

  <style>
    :root {
      --black: #0a0a0a;
      --white: #ffffff;
      --off-white: #f5f4f0;
      --accent: #ff4d00;
      --gray: #6b7280;
      --gray-light: #e5e7eb;
      --max-width: 820px;
    }

    .page-wrap {
      max-width: var(--max-width);
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 3rem 2rem 6rem;
    }

    .breadcrumb {
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: var(--gray);
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .breadcrumb a { color: var(--accent); }

    .page-tag {
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      color: var(--accent);
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: -0.04em;
      line-height: 1.1;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .intro {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      color: var(--gray);
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
      padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-light);
    }

    /* VERDICT BOX */
    .verdict-box {
      background: var(--black);
      color: var(--white);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 1.75rem 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 1.5rem;
    }

    .verdict-label {
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      color: var(--accent);
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    }

    .verdict-winner {
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    }

    .verdict-reason {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: #9ca3af;
      margin-top: 0.25rem;
    }

    /* COMPARISON TABLE */
    .compare-table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    .compare-table th {
      background: var(--black);
      color: var(--white);
      padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
      text-align: left;
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
    }

    .compare-table th:first-child { border-radius: 8px 0 0 0; }
    .compare-table th:last-child { border-radius: 0 8px 0 0; }

    .compare-table td {
      padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-light);
      vertical-align: top;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

    .compare-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--white); }
    .compare-table tr:nth-child(odd) td { background: #fafaf9; }

    .compare-table td:first-child {
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--gray);
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      width: 160px;
    }

    /* SECTIONS */
    .section { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }

    .section h2 {
      font-size: 1.3rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .section p {
      color: #374151;
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    /* AFFILIATE DISCLAIMER */
    .affiliate-note {
      background: #fef3f0;
      border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
      padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      color: var(--gray);
      border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    /* CTA */
    .bottom-cta {
      background: var(--off-white);
      border: 1px solid var(--gray-light);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 2rem;
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 3rem;
    }

    .bottom-cta h3 {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .bottom-cta p {
      color: var(--gray);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    }

    .btn-primary {
      background: var(--accent);
      color: var(--white);
      padding: 0.7rem 1.5rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      display: inline-block;
    }
  </style>

  <div class="page-wrap">

    <div class="breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a> → <a href="/compare">Compare</a> → {tool1} vs {tool2}
    </div>

    <div class="page-tag">Comparison · {category}</div>
    <h1>{tool1} vs {tool2}: The Honest Breakdown for Bootstrapped Founders</h1>

    <p class="intro">
      You don't need a 30-person marketing team's tool. You need the right tool for where you actually are. 
      This comparison skips the vendor fluff and tells you exactly which one makes sense — and when to switch.
    </p>

    <div class="affiliate-note">
      Some links below are affiliate links. We may earn a commission if you sign up — at no cost to you. 
      We only recommend tools we'd actually use.
    </div>

    <!-- VERDICT -->
    <div class="verdict-box">
      <div>
        <div class="verdict-label">Bootslapped Verdict</div>
        <div class="verdict-winner">→ {verdict} wins {verdictReason}</div>
        <div class="verdict-reason">Scroll down for the full breakdown and when to flip to {tool2}.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- COMPARISON TABLE -->
    <table class="compare-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th></th>
          <th>{tool1}</th>
          <th>{tool2}</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Free plan</td>
          <td>Yes — up to 500 contacts</td>
          <td>Yes — up to 250 contacts</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Starting price</td>
          <td>$13/mo (Essentials)</td>
          <td>$20/mo (Email)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Best for</td>
          <td>Getting started, simple newsletters</td>
          <td>E-commerce, deep segmentation</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Automation</td>
          <td>Basic on paid plans</td>
          <td>Advanced flows, strong</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Learning curve</td>
          <td>Low</td>
          <td>Medium-High</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Affiliate friendly</td>
          <td>Limited — ToS restrictions</td>
          <td>More flexible</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Integrations</td>
          <td>Wide (300+)</td>
          <td>Strong e-com focus</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <!-- SECTIONS -->
    <div class="section">
      <h2>When Mailchimp makes sense</h2>
      <p>
        If you're pre-revenue or early stage and just need a reliable way to send a newsletter and capture leads, 
        Mailchimp gets the job done without the learning curve. The free plan is generous enough to get your first 
        500 subscribers before you pay a dollar.
      </p>
      <p>
        The interface is familiar, the templates are decent, and you won't spend three hours figuring out how to 
        send your first campaign. For a bootstrapper who needs to move fast, that matters.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>When Klaviyo makes sense</h2>
      <p>
        Klaviyo earns its keep the moment you have a product and need behavioral triggers — abandoned cart, 
        post-purchase sequences, segment-based flows. If you're running an e-commerce business or a digital 
        product with meaningful purchase data, Klaviyo's segmentation is genuinely powerful.
      </p>
      <p>
        The learning curve is real. But if you're willing to spend a weekend with it, the automation ceiling 
        is much higher than Mailchimp.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>The honest verdict</h2>
      <p>
        Start with Mailchimp. Graduate to Klaviyo when you have purchase data worth segmenting and the time 
        to build proper flows. Most solo founders never actually need to make the switch — and that's fine.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bottom-cta">
      <h3>Still not sure which fits your setup?</h3>
      <p>Take the free Bootslapped diagnostic. 5 minutes and you'll know exactly what to prioritize.</p>
      <a href="/diagnostic" class="btn-primary">Take the Free Diagnostic →</a>
    </div>

  </div>

</Base>
